/19/1395243500834/255aab52-9d13-4470-9437-a3c0f6632fda-620x465.jpeg\" alt=\"Bibliotheque St Genevieve.\" width=\"620\" height=\"465\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption>Sainte-Geneviève library, Paris, France. The use of iron for the Ionic columns, highly innovative in its day, made it possible to do without cumbersome masonry. Henri Labrouste, 1851. Photograph: Laif/Camera Press.</figcaption> </figure>  <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"gu-fc-5da173d7-ec4f-45a6-bf9c-2d86350ed7a7\"> <img src=\"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2014/3/19/1395243585194/2a017c85-27b8-4c39-afcb-7e1cc11381b3-620x413.jpeg\" alt=\"Vennesla Library, Library, Europe, Norway, , 2012, Helen & Hard. View from rear of building at dusk.\" width=\"620\" height=\"413\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption>Vennesla library and culture house, Norway. The 'whale skeleton' structure and generous use of glass make this a bright, striking library that has become part of the urban fabric.  Helen &amp; Hard, 2011. Photograph: Hufton and Crow/VIEW</figcaption> </figure>  <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"gu-fc-d6eeb364-9fe6-4faf-9d14-be03d24026cc\"> <img src=\"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2014/3/19/1395243653047/5e03d5c5-4da5-4505-a5a6-6cd28d07fcdb-620x501.jpeg\" alt=\"Vennesla Library, Library, Europe, Norway, , 2012, Helen & Hard. View of interior at dusk.\" width=\"620\" height=\"501\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption>Vennesla library interior. Photograph: Hufton and Crow/VIEW</figcaption> </figure>  <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"gu-fc-84039cd6-90d5-4e3b-9bf5-6b888f0cc7ff\"> <img src=\"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2014/3/19/1395243920447/35c611df-5265-43e5-8cab-f808bc4157f5-319x480.jpeg\" alt=\"new bibliothek in luckenwaldefrom from ff architekten.\" width=\"319\" height=\"480\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption>Luckenwalde library, Germany: a converted rail